key_events.description: GARE11 sold 10 properties leased to Grupo Pão de Açúcar and Grupo Matheus.

key_events.event_name: Acquisition of Parque Logístico de Confins
key_events.description: Acquired Parque Logístico de Confins with tenants including Mercado Livre, Vale, and Três Corações, yielding over 10% per year for the first 60 months.

key_events.event_name: Acquisition of Corporate Building in Belo Horizonte
key_events.description: Acquired a corporate building in Belo Horizonte with long-term contracts and an estimated yield (Cap Rate) of 10.7% per year for the first 5 years (MRV headquarters).
Latest dividend was R$ 0.08 per share, translating to an annual dividend of 1.00 BRL per share, with a yield of 11.34%. Last ex-dividend date was Jan 2, 2026.
The fund concluded its 7th issuance of shares, with 141.7 million shares released for trading on January 14, 2026, priced at R$ 9.00 per share.

risk_factors: Fluctuations in tenant financial health impacting rental income.
Changes in market cap rates affecting property valuations.

investment_thesis.bull_case: Strategic acquisitions of high-yield properties like Parque Logístico de Confins and the MRV headquarters drive strong returns. Consistent dividend payments at R$0.08/share monthly, resulting in an 11.34% annual yield, attract income-focused investors.
investment_thesis.bear_case: Reliance on key tenants like Grupo Pão de Açúcar and Grupo Matheus exposes the fund to concentration risk. Potential dilution from the 7th issuance may temporarily suppress share price appreciation.

summary_markdown: GARE11 exhibits a mixed performance profile. Recent acquisitions, including Parque Logístico de Confins (yield >10% for 60 months) and a corporate building in Belo Horizonte (10.7% cap rate for 5 years), signal positive growth. The fund declared a dividend of R$0.08 per share (11.34% annual yield, ex-dividend date Jan 2, 2026). However, the sale of 10 properties leased to Grupo Pão de Açúcar and Grupo Matheus introduces uncertainty. The completion of the 7th issuance (141.7 million shares at R$9.00 on January 14, 2026) may dilute existing shareholders.
